headline: Why Palantir and These 3 Other Stocks Are Getting an Oracle Earnings Boost
summary: The artificial-intelligence trade was alive and well Wednesday after  Oracle fiscal first-quarter earnings pointed to surging demand for AI computing vendors.  Among the big names on the move, fellow AI cloud company  CoreWeave  popped 18%, AI chip maker  Advanced Micro Devices  was up 3.3%, and networking-equipment company  Arista Networks  was rising 5.9%.  Palantir Technologies  also got in on the action.
